text: A continuant is classified as a type of entity and also as a type of something that is only part of a continuant. It is distinct and separate from an occurrent as well as from something that is at least part of some occurrent. The definition of a continuant is an entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity, and has no temporal parts.

Occurrent is a type of entity and also a type of something that is only part of occurrent. It is disjoint with something that is at least part of some continuant. Moreover, occurrent is defined as an entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds, or develops through time.

An independent continuant is a type of continuant and is something that only a part of independent continuant can be. It is disjoint with specifically dependent continuant and also disjoint with generically dependent continuant. The definition of an independent continuant encompasses a continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything. Additionally, it is defined as b being an independent continuant, meaning b is a continuant which is such that there is no c and no t such that b s-depends on c at t, as per the axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [017-002].
A spatial region is categorized as a type of immaterial entity. It is distinct and separate from a site and also from a continuant fiat boundary.
The temporal region is a type of occurrent and is disjoint with the spatiotemporal region, process, and process boundary.
spatiotemporal region is a type of occurrent.

Process is categorized as a type of occurrent. It is defined as an occurrent that possesses temporal proper parts and, at some point in time t, is s-dependent on some material entity. Additionally, the definition of a process can be articulated as p being a process if and only if p is an occurrent that contains temporal proper parts and, for some time t, p s-depends on a material entity, as stated in the axiom labeled [083-003] in the BFO2 Reference.
Disposition is a type of realizable entity and it is disjoint with role.

Realizable entity is classified as a type of specifically dependent continuant and also as a type that is only part of realizable entity itself. It is distinct and separate from quality. The definition of a realizable entity is as follows: it is a specifically dependent continuant that inheres in continuant entities and is not exhibited in full at every moment it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity represents a particular manifestation, functioning, or process that occurs under certain circumstances.
Quality is a type of specifically dependent continuant and is also a type of something that is only part of quality.

Specifically dependent continuant is a type of continuant and is also defined as something that is only part of another specifically dependent continuant. It is distinct from and does not overlap with generically dependent continuant. Specifically dependent continuant is characterized by inhering in or being borne by other entities, where every instance of it requires a specific instance of another entity, which must always be the same. Moreover, there are multiple definitions provided for specifically dependent continuant. One definition states that a relational specifically dependent continuant, denoted as 'b', is a specifically dependent continuant that relies on more than one independent continuants, 'c1' to 'cn'. These independent continuants are not spatial regions and do not share common parts between any two distinct entities 'ci' and 'cj'. Additionally, for each independent continuant 'ci', 'b' depends on 'ci' at every moment during its existence, as referenced in BFO2 with the axiom label [131-004]. Another definition explains that a specifically dependent continuant, also represented as 'b', is a continuant that depends on some independent continuant 'c', which is not a spatial region. This dependency exists at every point in time during the continuant's existence, as noted in BFO2 with the axiom label [050-003].

A role is identical to another role and is also a type of role. Additionally, a role is defined as a realizable entity whose manifestation results in some outcome or end that is not essential to a continuant in virtue of the kind of thing it is. However, it can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant in various natural, social, or institutional contexts.
fiat object part is a type of material entity.
fiat object part is a type of material entity.
object aggregate is a type of material entity.
site is a type of immaterial entity.
object is a type of material entity.

A generically dependent continuant is a type of continuant and is also considered a type of something that is only part of a generically dependent continuant. It is defined as a continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers, where for every instance of it (A), requires some instance of an independent continuant type (B), but the specific instance of B can change over time. Additionally, the definition includes that b is a generically dependent continuant, described as b being a continuant that generically depends on one or more other entities, as indicated by the axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [074-001].
function is a type of disposition.

A process boundary is categorized as a type of occurrent. It is defined in the following manner: a process boundary is denoted as p, and it is said that p is a process boundary if and only if p is a temporal part of a process and p possesses no proper temporal parts. This definition is provided under the axiom label [084-001] in the BFO2 Reference.
one dimensional temporal region is a type of temporal region.

Material entity is a type of independent continuant and it has a definition as an independent continuant that is spatially extended, whose identity is independent of that of other entities, and can be maintained through time. It is disjoint with immaterial entity and also disjoint with something that is at least part of some immaterial entity.

Material entity is a type of independent continuant and is defined as an independent continuant that is spatially extended, whose identity is independent of that of other entities, and can be maintained through time. It is disjoint with immaterial entity and also disjoint with something that is at least part of some immaterial entity.

A continuant fiat boundary is categorized as a type of immaterial entity. It is defined in the following manner: b being a continuant fiat boundary entails that b is an immaterial entity characterized by being of zero, one, or two dimensions, and notably, it does not encompass a spatial region as a part. This definition is established under the axiom label [029-001] in the BFO2 Reference.
An immaterial entity is classified as a type of independent continuant. Additionally, it is disjoint from anything that possesses, at least in part, some material entity.
A one-dimensional continuant fiat boundary is a type of continuant fiat boundary and is disjoint with a two-dimensional continuant fiat boundary.
two dimensional continuant fiat boundary is a type of continuant fiat boundary.

text: Ammonia is identified as a type of gas molecular entity, azane, and mononuclear parent hydride. It is defined as an azane that consists of a single nitrogen atom covalently bonded to three hydrogen atoms. Ammonia is exactly synonymous with AMMONIA, Ammonia, ammonia, and azane. Additionally, it has related synonyms including Ammoniak, NH3, R-717, [NH3], ammoniac, amoniaco, and spirit of hartshorn.
Hydrogen sulfide is categorized as a gas molecular entity, a hydracid, a sulfur hydride, and a mononuclear parent hydride.
Methane is a type of gas molecular entity, alkane, mononuclear parent hydride, and one carbon compound.

text: Sulfate is identified as a type of sulfur oxoanion, sulfur oxide, and a divalent inorganic anion. It is defined as a sulfur oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of both OH groups of sulfuric acid. Sulfate is exactly synonymous with Sulfate, sulfate, tetraoxidosulfate(2-), tetraoxosulfate(2-), and tetraoxosulfate(VI). Additionally, it has related synonyms such as SO4(2-), SULFATE ION, Sulfate anion(2-), Sulfate dianion, Sulfate(2-), Sulfuric acid ion(2-), [SO4](2-), sulphate, and sulphate ion.

:carbohydrate rdfs:subClassOf :carbohydrates_and_carbohydrate_derivatives ;
    :has_definition "Any member of the class of organooxygen compounds that is a polyhydroxy-aldehyde or -ketone or a lactol resulting from their intramolecular condensation (monosaccharides); substances derived from these by reduction of the carbonyl group (alditols), by oxidation of one or more hydroxy groups to afford the corresponding aldehydes, ketones, or carboxylic acids, or by replacement of one or more hydroxy group(s) by a hydrogen atom; and polymeric products arising by intermolecular acetal formation between two or more such molecules (disaccharides, polysaccharides and oligosaccharides). Carbohydrates contain only carbon, hydrogen and oxygen atoms; prior to any oxidation or reduction, most have the empirical formula Cm(H2O)n. Compounds obtained from carbohydrates by substitution, etc., are known as carbohydrate derivatives and may contain other elements. Cyclitols are generally not regarded as carbohydrates." ;
    :has_exact_synonym "carbohydrate",
        "carbohydrates" ;
    :has_related_synonym "Kohlenhydrat",
        "Kohlenhydrate",
        "a carbohydrate",
        "carbohidrato",
        "carbohidratos",
        "glucide",
        "glucides",
        "glucido",
        "glucidos",
        "hydrates de carbone",
        "saccharide",
        "saccharides",
        "saccharidum" .
text: Carbohydrate is a type of carbohydrates and carbohydrate derivatives, defined as any member of the class of organooxygen compounds that include polyhydroxy-aldehyde or -ketone, or a lactol resulting from their intramolecular condensation (monosaccharides); substances derived from these by reduction of the carbonyl group (alditols), by oxidation of one or more hydroxy groups to afford the corresponding aldehydes, ketones, or carboxylic acids, or by replacement of one or more hydroxy group(s) by a hydrogen atom; and polymeric products arising by intermolecular acetal formation between two or more such molecules (disaccharides, polysaccharides, and oligosaccharides). Carbohydrates contain only carbon, hydrogen, and oxygen atoms; prior to any oxidation or reduction, most have the empirical formula Cm(H2O)n. Compounds obtained from carbohydrates by substitution, etc., are known as carbohydrate derivatives and may contain other elements. Cyclitols are generally not regarded as carbohydrates. Carbohydrate has exact synonyms "carbohydrate" and "carbohydrates," and related synonyms include "Kohlenhydrat," "Kohlenhydrate," "a carbohydrate," "carbohidrato," "carbohidratos," "glucide," "glucides," "glucido," "glucidos," "hydrates de carbone," "saccharide," "saccharides," and "saccharidum."

text: Polysaccharide is a type of carbohydrate, glycan, and biomacromolecule. It is defined as a biomacromolecule consisting of large numbers of monosaccharide residues linked glycosidically, commonly used only for those containing more than ten monosaccharide residues. Polysaccharide has exact synonyms such as "Polysaccharide" and "polysaccharides." Additionally, it has related synonyms, including "Glycan," "Glycane," "Glykan," "Glykane," "glycans," "polisacarido," and "polisacaridos."
